# Sentry DSN for crash reporting (leave empty to disable)
#
# This template is designed for a self-hosted Sentry instance.
# Deploy your own: https://develop.sentry.dev/self-hosted/
#
# After deployment, create a project in Sentry UI and copy the DSN.
# Format: http://<public_key>@<host>:<port>/<project_id>
#
# Example for local Docker deployment:
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=http://8550a56f41fc3c8a4f0ca8ec5f8acfde@127.0.0.1:9000/2
#
# This variable is validated at build time by @t3-oss/env-core + zod.
# It must be a valid URL or an empty string. Invalid values will cause
# the build to fail with a clear error message.
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
